Essence £10 make-up challenge and reviews 
I was sent some make-up from Essence, an established European beauty brand that launched in the UK earlier this year, and challenged to make up my face with just £10 of Essence cosmetics. I used to love seeing the colourful Essence displays in continental Europe and once bought a spot gel from the brand (“anti-pickel gel” haha) but this is my first ... is a standard bristly one. I normally get better results with plastic/rubbery bristles so I’d be up for looking at other Essence mascaras with that kind of wand to see if they give more effect on me.

Overall, I think the Essence brand is cute, affordable and well worth a look. There will be some misses amongst the hits (e.g. the liquid ... but the quality is much better than the prices suggest, and I really do love the cream to powder blusher.
Essence cosmetics are available from Wilko stores (and Wilko.com) or at standalone Essence stores in Westfield West London and Manchester Arndale. You can also see the range of products on the Essence website.

Essence Cosmetics Long Lasting Lipsticks – Review, Swatches & Photos What Essence Cosmetics Claims
“Long lasting love… you simply have to fall in love with the longlasting lipsticks by essence. the lipsticks provide your lips with intensive color for several hours without drying them out. you’re sure to find whatever you’re looking for – from bright pink to intensive red and chilled-out berry to subtle nude shades. the essence logo on the texture and the matt, black packaging with a ring of color to match the actual color of the lipstick are true eye-catchers!” 
Originating in Germany, Essence Cosmetics is an affordable drugstore makeup brand that has made it’s way to Canada. Exclusively available at Shoppers Drug Mart ... known for it’s cute packaging and variety of different fun colors.
Currently available in a total of 10 shades the Essence Cosmetics Long Lasting lipsticks come in a sleek matte black tube that is honestly too good for the price. I ... not like these lipsticks but it doesn’t linger on after you apply it. 
Now on to the pigmentation. Unlike the Essence Lipsticks I reviewed recently, these lipsticks are a lot more pigmented which is a nice change. I wouldn’t go as ... very creamy and surprisingly very moisturizing. I love that these lipsticks don’t have any shimmer or frost like the other Essence lipsticks. The finish does remind me of the MAC Amplified lipsticks except these lipsticks are not as thick.

Beauty Favourites - Top 14 of 2014 Let's just say I tried a few beauty products in 2014. Actually, to be honest, its more than a few...probably into the hundreds. But I took one for the team and from exciting new releases to old favourites and cult products I've put together a list of my top 14 products of 2014. Enjoy!FACE1// Maybelline Fit Me Concealer ($14.95)To be honest, I always felt I had to rely on high end products for my base but this concealer from Maybelline is incredible for the price. Perfect for under the eyes, on blemishes and to cover redness this is definitely by no.1 drugstore recommendation.Review2// The Body Shop Honey Bronzer ($22.95)I don't think I have once used another bronzer since I picked this one up. Using a big fluffy brush adding a natural bronze to my face with this product is practically fool proof. A beautiful bronze shade that isn't orange at all and perfect for all skin tones as it comes in three shades. It's also really blend able and will last all day. Worth the investment!Review3// MAC Powder Blush in 'Melba' ($41.00)This is everything you want in a blush - it blends beautifully, looks gorgeous on any skin tone and with any look and most importantly is a pretty great colour. Melba is one of those blushers I reached for when I didn't know what blush to wear. If you are just starting out with makeup or looking for a new signature blush, pop into a MAC store and try Melba - you won't be disappointed.SwatchesEYES4// Maybelline The Falsies Mascara ($19.95)Another AWESOME find from the drugstore and once again Maybelline offers excellent value. The formula is great - not too wet or dry - and easy to work with along with a great want. It will last all day without smudging or flaking either. My favourite choice for thick, long lashes without much of a fuss.Review5// Lancôme Hypnose Mascara ($52.00)My favourite ever mascara of all time! If you've read my blog all year you'll know I rave about this product a lot and it's been one of my favourite makeup products even before my makeup obsession when I wore makeup about three times a year. It's definitely a splurge item that I believe is worth the price tag. Unlike the mascara from Maybelline, this mascara will last longer, never irritate your eyes and with just one layer separate your lashes whilst adding amazing length and the perfect amount of volume every time.Review6// Maybelline Colour Tattoo in 'Bad to the Bronze' ($11.95)Yep, another amazing Maybelline product. The Colour Tattoos are cream eyeshadows that are perfect for that smokey eye look with about zero effort. Sweep over the eyelid using either your finger or a synthetic brush and voila! Easiest eye look ever. As the name 'tattoo' suggests, these really don't budge once you've applied them so they are a perfect eyeshadow option for summer. While 'Bad to the Bronze' is my favourite shade to wear on its own, I've got heaps of other shades that I like to use as a base for other eyeshadows to create extra dimension to my eye look.Review7// NYX Jumbo Eye Pencil in 'Milk' ($9.95)Milk is the ultimate cult beauty product. It's not a new release by any means and a permanent addition to the NYX line but finding in stock is a mission. I wear this everyday as a highlight under my brows and it also makes an awesome eyeshadow primer. A great all-round product which is proven by it's popularity. If you're in Target, swing past the NYX stand to see if you can find one in stock - in which case you should buy it.8// NARS Larger Than Life Long-Wear Eyeliner in 'Rue Bonaparte' ($32.00)A product I've mentioned in my monthly roundup posts countless times this year because it really is one of my favourite products ever. I haven't yet found another eye pencil that stays in the waterline no matter what. It has a high price tag, especially for a pencil but well worth the money and you'll definitely get a lot of use out of it. With any makeup look this looks amazing on the waterline to make your eyes look bigger and brighter.Review9// Benefit Gimme Brow ($32.00)2014 was the year of the brow and the search was on for the perfect brow product. I'm pretty happy with how far my brows have come this year and I have Benefit to thank for that. Apart from regular appointments to get a wax and tint the Benefit Gimme Brow worked to add a little bit of colour and hold those stray brow hairs in place. Literally the perfect brow gel with the handiest little wand making to super easy to apply too. My pick of the brow products this year!ReviewLIPS10// MAC Lipstick in 'Plumful' ($36.00)In my makeup explorations of 2014, I definitely tried more lipsticks than any other type of product. Plumful was my most worn and favourite shade meaning it is definitely an amazing product. A soft, rosy-purple shade in MAC's Lustre formula Plumful is not only super pretty on the lips but really comfortable to wear and moisturising too.ReviewNAILS - Reviews11// Sally Hansen Insta- Dri Topcoat ($15.45)If 2014 was a quest, it would

あぁ〜本当に落ち着く、、、
零れ落ちそうに満開の薔薇の香りを嗅ぎながら、
今日のボディケアには
しっとりと静かな
#リケンデコス の香りを。
こちらは、苔 をメインにした香りなんです。
#オフィシーヌユニヴェルセルビュリー  の#水性香水 と同じ香りの#ボディオイル 
クラシカルなボトルも、素敵です。
*
#ディプティック のキャンドルの「苔の香り(ムース)」が大好きで、昔何度もリピートしていました。
ここ数年はお香派でキャンドルからは離れていましたが、ビュリーで久々に「苔の香り」と出会いました。
しかもキャンドルなどルームフレグランスではなく、身体に付けるオイルや香水のメインが苔だなんてなかなか攻めてますネ
苔の香りは香水のベースノートに配合されることはありますが、メインになる事は少ないエッセンス。
#ビュリー の#lichendecosse  は、苔のしっとり青く少しムワッとした落ち着きのある香りと、鉱物のキンとしたヒンヤリ感が独特。あと、ちょっと甘酸っぱいフルーティ感も感じるのだけど・・・青いカシスのような。何のフルーツだろう?✨
不思議にハマる香りです。
ボディローションもありますが、ボディオイルの方が香りがしっかりめ。
水性香水(#オートリプル)なら、香り持ちが長く柔らかな香りを楽しめます。香水の方がオイルよりちょっとグリーン感が控えめでまろみがあるように感じましたよ。このあたりは、好みで選ぶと良いかと
*
*
#ユイルアンティーク のベースオイルは・・・ココナッツオイルなどが入っている・・・と伺った気がしますが、#ドライオイル タイプでサラリとしていてベタつきません。
これからの季節にピッタリ!!
保湿を重視したい方ならボディミルク#レヴィジナル が良いかな。香りはオイルより控えめです。
*
*
リケンデコスは、私に「似合う」かどうかだと・・・水性香水を購入した#ヘリオトロープデュペルー の方がしっくり来るかも。
でも好みで言うと、こういう落ち着きのある香り、実は大好物です!!
リケンデコスを全身につけて眠るのが最近のブームです。

GINZA SIX内の数ある店舗の中でも一際目を惹く、細胞をイメージした「センターテーブル」と天井の「光のアートワーク」は、建築家・田根剛さんのデザイン。
足を一歩踏み入れると床にはふかふかの絨毯、シナクティフのエステルーム(予約制)があったり、音響や天井の光さえも日によって変わる演出がされていてまさにクレ・ド・ポー ボーテに相応しい空間。
・
1996年からリニューアルし続け、
シルクのエッセンスを配合、まるで宝石のような美しさで「6万円のクリーム」としてブランドを象徴し女性の憧れであるあのラ・クレーム クリームを使用した贅沢なサービスが、ギンザシックス店限定でスタート。
ラ・クレームを使用したハンドマッサージがなんと無料で体験できるというもの!(予約制ではないので店舗に直接行ってみて下さい)

Este año @essence_cosmetics cumple 15 años y ha preparado una fiesta celebración el 15 de julio en Berlín y he tenido el privilegio ... ahí, también ha invitado a una de vosotr@s con un acompañante! Quien se quiere venir conmigo a la fiesta de @essence_cosmetics en Berlin??? Ahora para elegir a la persona lo haré en forma aleatoria pero para participar lo voy a hacer ... *1 noche de alojamiento + desayuno en habitación doble, hotel Nhow Berlin. *Traslado desde el hotel a la fiesta de Essence.
*2 entradas para la fiesta del 15 aniversario.
*Lote de productos

Quien puede participar: *Mayores de 18 años. *Que dispongan ... vivan en España.

Como participar: 
1.Ser seguidora de mi perfil de instagram @silviaquiros 
2.Ser seguidora del perfil de instagram de @essence_cosmetics 
3.Recrear un maquillaje usando tu producto favorito de Essence (no se valorará la calidad del maquillaje)
4.Publicar una foto en tu perfil de instagram enseñando el look y el producto (tal como ves que he hecho yo en esta foto) etiquetándome a mi, a Essence y añadiendo los hashtags #essencebirthdaybash #15pinkyears (si no se añaden los hashtag quedara descalificada) y debes tener el perfil en público hasta por lo menos ... en contacto con ella (o el) y tendrá 24 horas para responder, pasado ese tiempo elegiré a otra.
Suerte! Tagged: @essence_cosmetics

Oggi vi mostro lo smalto della settimana, il numero 94 'Kiss the freaky frog' (bellissimo il nome ) di Essence... direi che si tratta di un verde acqua! 
La colorazione mi piace tantissimo, è allegra ed estiva... anche se io ... coat. Il pennellino è abbastanza grande e l'asciugatura rapida. 
So che molte ragazze non si trovano bene con gli smalti Essence, soprattutto per quanto riguarda la durata... a me piacciono molto invece! ☺
Come dico sempre, su di me gli smalti durano poco (mi scordo una durata superiore a una settimana come capita ad alcune ragazze )... però questi Essence, per quanto dipenda da colore a colore, sono sicuramente nella media dei miei smalti! Anzi, ho un color marsala che ... più smalti, ma in futuro prenderò sicuramente qualche altro colore di questa linea!

Essence 2 in 1 Eyeshadow and Primer 02 Nude Rose Review Hello everyone!
A perfect base makeup for your face and ... own, it can also be used as a base to make your favourite eye shadow last longer.
My Experience with Essence 2 in 1 Eyeshadow and Primer 02 Nude Rose:
I wanted to buy MAC Painterly Paint Pot, but when I came across the Essence primer, I changed my mind looking at the price tag. This brand offers such amazing quality makeup at such an affordable price. I love Essence for its eye makeup products, especially mascara, kajal, eyeliner (I’ll be reviewing them soon), gel nail polishes and much more. ... I have a tough time working with eyeshadows that are less pigmented and have a low staying power. And, this Essence primer fixes everything like magic. It enhances the shade of the eyeshadow and makes it last a long time. Even ... in 1 formula that works as an eyeshadow and primer both, I use this only for priming purpose.  

Pros of Essence 2 in 1 Eyeshadow and Primer 02 Nude Rose:
• Creamy texture.
• Glides easily.
• Easy to blend.
• ... the skin tone.
• Makes the eyeshadow last long.
• I quite love the packaging too.
• Price.
Cons of Essence 2 in 1 Eyeshadow and Primer 02 Nude Rose:
• Doesn’t have an applicator.
• Looks a little chalky as an eyeshadow. 
IMBB Rating: 4.9/5
Would I Repurchase Essence 2 in 1 Eyeshadow and Primer 02 Nude Rose?
Yes! I would love to repurchase this once I finish this product. In fact, now I’m eyeing the first shade “01 Nude Beige” as well.
Would I Recommend Essence 2 in 1 Eyeshadow and Primer 02 Nude Rose?
Yes! I highly recommend buying this one. I think you should go get it soon before it runs out of stock. This one is an absolute steal for the price.

Recensione Rossetti Lips Go Wow Lip Art Palette Essence INTRODUZIONE & INCI
Iniziamo questo 2018 con una recensione dedicata ad un prodotto per le nostre labbra, ideato per creare infiniti look. Di cosa stiamo parlando? Della Lips Go Wow Lip Art Palette di Essence!
All’interno contiene quattro rossetti dalla texture, secondo il brand, cremosa e dal finish cipriato. A quanto pare i colori possono ... mixarli tra di loro). Curiose di scoprire tutto su questa palette? Allora iniziamo subito! 


LIPS GO WOW LIP ART PALETTE ESSENCE
All’interno ci sono 6g di prodotto totali mentre, dalla data di apertura, dura 12 mesi. Il prezzo è di 4,49€ ... Be An Artist che potete vedere sia con luce naturale che con luce artificiale.
Lips Go Wow Lip Art Palette Essence in Be An Artist, swatch realizzato con luce naturale.
Lips Go Wow Lip Art Palette Essence in Be An Artist, swatch realizzato con luce artificiale.
Come detto dal brand la texture di questi rossetti è cremosa ... il “dopo” potete capire meglio il livello di pigmentazione dei rossetti presenti nella palette.
Lips Go Wow Lip Art Palette Essence in Be An Artist, fotografia realizzata con luce naturale.
Lips Go Wow Lip Art Palette Essence in Be An Artist, fotografia realizzata con luce artificiale.
Qui sopra potete vedere il primo colore, una sorta di malva ... il rosa Barbie, sono gli unici due in grado di coprire abbastanza le labbra.
Lips Go Wow Lip Art Palette Essence in Be An Artist, fotografia realizzata con luce naturale.
